            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>Thomas Walton, who graduated from the University of Illinois in 1911, became Education Director of the campus Y.M.C.A. in 1914. This collection contains his handwritten draft (on 70 half-size sheets of paper) of &quot;The Spending of Home Mission Money in Illinois.&quot; He based his paper on interviews with church officials and on a questionaire sent to pastors of major Protestant denominations. The collection also includes a copy of Walton&#039;s University of Illinois grades.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


